UNITED STATES: Former Governor of California and actor, Arnold Schwarzenegger, aka 'The Terminator', had a blunt message for President Trump regarding his attempts to force energy utilities to buy coal power. READ: Schwarzenegger moves from 'Terminator' to climate change 'innovator' Schwarzenegger released a video mocking Trump's drive to support the coal industry, likening it to supporting the failed Blockbuster video chai over Netflix. *View the attached video of Schwarzenegger's hilarious take on Trump's energy policy, a continuation of the long-standing animosity between the two larger-than-life American public figures. YouTube